Director Core Engineering (IT)· Singapore, Singapore
Director Core Engineering (IT)
Singapore, Singapore
Full Time Employment
Recruiter Comment: We are on the lookout for a Core IT Director to join our client in leading and managing the Group IT Global Infrastructure and Technology department to deliver all IT Infrastructure & Technology Services. #Singapore #Jobs #ITDirector
Share:Job DescriptionThis position is responsible for leading and managing the Group IT Global Infrastructure and Technology (I&T) department to deliverall the infrastructure and technology services, systems and projects to support all the business units technology lifecycle management including trends, architecture, planning, blueprinting, designing, implementation and reviewingIT governance includes guidelines, policies and standardsResponsibilitiesWork with Portfolio Heads and Application Suite Owners to plan and implement initiatives to ensure a cost effective, high performing, reliable and available global IT infrastructure;Ensure all IT services, systems and projects are delivered on time, on budget, and meet the business and quality requirements;Work with Business Project Sponsors and IT Project Directors to develop multi-year budget and work plan for the infrastructure components of projects, and supervise the timely and successful implementation of these infrastructure components;Work with VP and Integration, on the integration of legacy and systems;Ensure compliance with all relevant corporate policies and procedures;Ensure minimal audit findings by internal and external audits, and where required, complete follow up actions promptly;Supervise, coach, motivate and develop IT employees;Mentor selected Group IT employees; andAssist the Group CIO in planning and executing organisation development related initiatives.Work and interfaces with other teams within Group IT that are well coordinated and aligned to meet the over-arching goals of Group IT.Guide and assist business units (application suite owners) to define suitable business metrics that result in business actions which lead to positive business outcomes via IT services, systems and projects delivered schedule, on budget and that meet business requirements;External and internal customers who are satisfied with the performance and availability of our application systems and IT servicesRequirementsBachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Business Administration, or other related field.  Or equivalent work experience.More than 15 years of working experience in IT, out of which about 10 years of experience in leading and managing teams of IT professionalsMore than 5 years of experience in managing an IT organisation that outsources extensively; strong experience in IT contracts and vendor managementMore than 5 years of experience in managing distributed, multi-country, 24X7 infrastructure planning and operationsProven track record in managing complex IT projects that involve vendor(s), business users and internal IT team working together collectively to deliver resultsTechnical Breadth – Sufficient mastery across the IT technology disciplines (host processing. Networking, security, data management, business continuity, application development and systems management) to enable integrated planning, management and oversight across these functional areas. The candidate will be a recognized authority in the area of technology planning and oversight.Communication Skills – Communicates clearly and effectively at all levels in a range of methods (written, verbal, formal presentation)Business acumen – Knows how business works; knowledgeable in current and possible future policies, practice, trends, developments in e-commerce and information affecting his/her business and organization; knows the competition; is aware of how strategies and tactics work in the marketplaceProblem management skills – Lead complex problem resolution that requires the involvement of cross functional and cross organizational cooperation in resolving critical issues.Customer Focus – Dedicated to meeting the expectations and requirements of internal and external customers; establishes and maintains effective relationships with customers and gains their trust and respect. Understands long term customer needs and leads the alignment across organizations to plan and enable the satisfaction of these requirements.Stakeholder management – Able to understand and relate with key stakeholders, able to influence them using a variety of inter-personal skills, professional knowledge and work experience.This position requires some amount of travelling, once every 3 – 4 months.Please send your resume in WORD format to john.lee@lysten.com.sg or contact John Lee on +65 6332 0139 for a confidential discussion. Please note that only short-listed candidates will be contacted.ProfileYour IT Trained Recruiter
